snippet.title: Cambridge, July 5, 1858. [electronic resource] : The proposed purchase of Mt. Vernon is an object of interest to every American. Old and young, rich and poor, learned and uneducated, all hope for its success, and wish to aid it. The organization of the "Ladies' Mt. Vernon Association of the Union" is now complete. ... The undersigned, having been appointed by the regent, Miss Ann Pamela Cunningham, vice-regent for Massachusetts, and having obtained the counsel and co-operation of the gentlemen whose names are found below, confidently appeals to the community to do their part toward promoting an object which must recommend itself to every American heart. ...
